{
  "texts": [
    "While computationally efficient, it may converge slowly for complex models and datasets.",
    "Careful tuning of initial learning rates is often needed.",
    "-Adam: Combines features of SGD with adaptive learning rates and momentum to accelerate convergence and reduce the risk of getting stuck in local minima.",
    "Requires tuning of hyperparameters like beta1 and beta2 and is suitable for nonstationary and noisy objectives.",
    "-Adagrad: An adaptive algorithm adjusting learning rates based on parameter update frequency."
  ]
}